duction%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20special%20inspector%20general%20report%20to%20Congress%20on%20Operation%20Atlantic%20Resolve%20released%20on%20Thursday%20said%2C%20highlighting%20the%20ammo%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20more%2C%20it%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20Ukrainian%20military's%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20rate%20of%20fire%20has%20also%20had%20a%20correlating%20impact%20on%20the%20maintenance%20of%20its%20domestic%20and%20internationally%20donated%20artillery%20systems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20report%20explained%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20extremely%20active%20employment%20of%20these%20weapons%2C%20coupled%20with%20limited%20spare%20parts%2C%20has%20resulted%20in%20weapons%20being%20fired%20beyond%20their%20recommend%20maintenance%20or%20replacement%20schedules.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20using%20limited%20artillery%20beyond%20intended%20use%20can%20result%20in%20%26quot%3Bcatastrophic%20failure%20of%20the%20gun%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Binjury%20or%20death%20of%20the%20cannon%20crew%20members.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20war%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20using%20a%20mix%20of%20Soviet%20and%20Western%20military%20systems%2C%20raising%20issues%20involving%20%26quot%3Bobtaining%20spare%20parts%2C%20maintenance%20solutions%2C%20and%20technical%20expertise%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20new%20special%20inspector%20general%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20been%20prioritizing%20the%20use%20of%20unmanned%20aerial%20systems%20for%20strike%20missions%2C%20surveillance%2C%20and%20the%20direction%20of%20fires.%20With%20less%20ammunition%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20to%20shoot%20smarter.%20Its%20drones%20appear%20to%20work%20well%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraines-military-is-using-drones-to-make-ammunition-more-accurate-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20tandem%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20artillery%2C%20boosting%20accuracy%20by%20250%20percent%2C%20soldiers%20say.%20Still%2C%20the%20country's%20wartime%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eresources%20are%20extremely%20depleted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMessaging%20from%20Ukrainian%20leadership%20and%20requests%20from%20the%20UAF%20have%20consistently%20attempted%20to%20secure%20a%20continued%20supply%20of%20munitions%20from%20the%20international%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20special%20inspector%20general's%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20been%20unable%20to%20secure%20more%20US%20aid%20lately%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20if%20it%20continues%20to%20be%20held%20up%20in%20Congress%2C%20the%20Ukrainian%20military%20may%20be%20under%20additional%20pressure.%20There's%20a%20risk%20it%20could%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frepublicans-could-be-about-to-cost-ukraine-war-analysts-russia-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20it%20the%20war%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iiss.org%2Fonline-analysis%2Fmilitary-balance%2F2024%2F02%2Fequipment-losses-in-russias-war-on-ukraine-mount%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EInternational%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iiss.org%2Fonline-analysis%2Fmilitary-balance%2F2024%2F02%2Fequipment-losses-in-russias-war-on-ukraine-mount%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20that%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E'%3C%2Fu%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iiss.org%2Fonline-analysis%2Fmilitary-balance%2F2024%2F02%2Fequipment-losses-in-russias-war-on-ukraine-mount%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Es%20overall%20lack%20of%20equipment%20and%20supplies%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20left%20it%20unable%20to%20field%20new%20combat%20elements%20at%20full%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20has%20been%20producing%20enough%20tanks%2C%20combat%20vehicles%2C%20and%20other%20equipment%20and%20has%20enough%20in%20storage%20and%20