ces%20Bela%20M%20Trivedi%20and%20Pankaj%20Mithal%20that%20first%20and%20foremost%2C%20the%20duty%20of%20a%20lawyer%20is%20towards%20the%20court%20to%20assist%20it%20in%20a%20settlement%20of%20law%20and%20not%20his%20client.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bar%20bodies%2C%20such%20as%20Bar%20Council%20of%20India%2C%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20Bar%20Association%20and%20Bar%20of%20Indian%20Lawyers%2C%20and%20other%20individuals%20in%20a%20batch%20of%20petitions%20have%20challenged%20a%202007%20verdict%20of%20the%20National%20Consumer%20Disputes%20Redressal%20Commission%20(NCDRC)%2C%20which%20has%20ruled%20that%20advocates%20and%20their%20services%20come%20under%20the%20purview%20of%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%2C%201986.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReplying%20to%20the%20court's%20observation%20made%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20if%20doctors%20can%20be%20sued%20for%20poor%20service%20and%20negligence%20and%20deficiency%20in%20service%2C%20then%20why%20can't%20lawyers%2C%20Mr%20Hooda%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20doctor's%20clinic%20has%20been%20treated%20as%20a%20commercial%20entity%20like%20all%20big%20hospitals%2C%20which%20can%20advertise%20themselves.%20There%20is%20no%20bar%20on%20them.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20a%20bar%20on%20lawyers%20to%20advertise%20their%20work.%20They%20cannot%20solicit%20work%20and%20cannot%20have%20a%20share%20in%20the%20suit%20property%20as%20the%20remuneration%20for%20their%20service%20under%20the%20Advocates%20Act%20of%201961.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssailing%20the%20NCDRC%20verdict%2C%20Mr%20Hooda%20said%20lawyers%20stand%20on%20a%20different%20footing%20than%20doctors%20or%20any%20other%20professionals%20due%20to%20the%20restrictions%20provided%20under%20the%201961%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20for%20professional%20misconduct%2C%20there%20is%20already%20a%20remedy%20provided%20for%20a%20litigant%20to%20lodge%20a%20complaint%20with%20the%20Bar%20Council%20of%20India%2C%20besides%20the%20option%20of%20approaching%20a%20court%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20not%20that%20lawyers%20have%20immunity%20against%20a%20complaint%20filed%20by%20a%20litigant.%20A%20remedy%20for%20loss%20can%20go%20to%20the%20civil%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Hooda%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20when%20the%20Advocates%20Act%20came%20into%20force%20in%201961%2C%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%20of%201986%20was%20nowhere%20on%20the%20horizon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%201986%20law%20was%20conceived%20with%20an%20altogether%20different%20intent%20to%20protect%20the%20interest%20of%20even%20a%20small%20consumer%20from%20the%20mighty%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%20was%20conceived%20in%20such%20a%20manner%20that%20the%20services%20rendered%20by%20a%20lawyer%20do%20not%20fit%20in%20like%20any%20other%20services%20rendered%20in%20other%20professions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20senior%20lawyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20under%20the%201986%20law%2C%20a%20consumer%20can%20file%20a%20complaint%20by%20just%20writing%20a%20two-page%20letter%20and%20the%20consumer%20forum%20has%20to%20take%20a%20decision%20on%20it%20on%20merit%20even%20in%20his%20absence%2C%20whereas%20a%20litigant%20has%20to%20hire%20a%20lawyer%20to%20contest%20a%20court%20case%20and%20sign%20a%20%26quot%3Bvakalatnama%26quot%3B%2C%20authorising%20the%20lawyer%20to%20argue%20the%20case%20on%20his%20behalf.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hearing%20remained%20inconclusive%20and%20would%20continue%20on%20February%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%202007%20judgment%2C%20the%20consumer%20commission%20had%20held%20that%20advocates%20come%20under%20the%20purview%20of%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%20and%20can%20be%20sued%20in%20a%20consumer%20court%20by%20their%20clients%20for%20any%20deficiency%20in%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20national%20consumer%20forum's%20verdict%20had%20held%20that%20the%20legal%20services%20rendered%20by%20lawyers%20would%20come%20within%20the%20ambit%20of%20section%202(1)(o)%20of%20the%201986%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%202(1)(o)%20of%20the%20Act%20defines%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Bservice%26quot%3B%20to%20mean%20a%20%26quot%3Bservice%20of%20any%20description%2C%20which%20is%20made%20available%20to%20potential%20users%20and%20includes%2C%20but%20not%20limited%20to%2C%20the%20provision%20of%20facilities%20in%20connection%20with%20banking%2C%20financing%20insurance%2C%20transport%2C%20processing%2C%20supply%20of%20electrical%20or%20other%20energy%2C%20board%20or%20lodging%20or%20both%2C%20housing%20construction%2C%20entertainment%2C%20amusement%20or%20the%20purveying%20of%20news%20or%20other%20information%2C%20but%20does%20not%20include%20the%20rendering%20of%20any%20service%20free%20of%20charge%20or%20under%20a%20contract%20of%20personal%20service%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUndisputedly%2C%20lawyers%20are%20rendering%20service.%20They%20are%20charging%20fees.%20It%20is%20not%20a%20contract%20of%20personal%20service.%20Therefore%2C%20there%20is%20no%20reason%20to%20hold%20that%20they%20are%20not%20covered%20by%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%2C%201986%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20NCDRC%20had%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%2C%20however%2C%20stayed%20the%20August%206%2C%202007%20verdict%20of%20the%20NCDRC%20in%20April%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708020000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-07%2Fatt9hsso_court-generic_625x300_27_July_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flawyers-services-cant-be-under-consumer-protection-law-bar-associations-to-court-5065394%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20told%20on%20Thursday%20that%20lawyers%20or%20legal%20practitioners%20cannot%20solicit%