bruary%2019%2C%202024.%20Their%20friendship%20grew%20stronger%20after%20a%20small%20disagreement%20about%20scheduling%20issues.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fmilan-luthria-shares-why-he-was-angry-with-ajay-devgn-while-shooting-kachche-dhaage%2Farticleshow%2F107730251.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Electoral%20Bonds%20Scheme%20Violative%20of%20Voter%E2%80%99s%20Right%20to%20Information%3A%20Top%20Quotes%20From%20the%20Supreme%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Thursday%20(February%2015)%20delivered%20its%20judgment%20on%20petitions%20contesting%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20ruling%20it%20as%20violative%20of%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20and%20unconstitutional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%2C%20consisting%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20along%20with%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%2C%20BR%20Gavai%2C%20JB%20Pardiwala%2C%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20delivered%20two%20separate%20but%20unanimous%20verdicts%20on%20the%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20scheme.%20Having%20reserved%20the%20verdict%20on%20November%202%2C%202023%2C%20the%20five-judge%20bench%20concluded%20the%20deliberations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20in%202018%20and%20allowed%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%20Under%20this%20system%2C%20individuals%20or%20entities%20could%20purchase%20electoral%20bonds%20from%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20and%20allocate%20them%20to%20a%20political%20party%20of%20their%20preference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpart-of-secret-ballot-how-the-modi-govt-backed-electoral-bonds-in-the-supreme-court%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Part%20of%20Secret%20Ballot%E2%80%99%3A%20How%20the%20Modi%20Govt%20Backed%20Electoral%20Bonds%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20scheme%2C%20only%20the%20political%20parties%20registered%20under%20Section%2029A%20of%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201951%20and%20which%20secured%20not%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20the%20votes%20polled%20in%20the%20last%20elections%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20or%20a%20state%20legislative%20assembly%20are%20eligible%20to%20receive%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElectoral%20bonds%20worth%20more%20than%20Rs%20570%20crores%20have%20been%20sold%20in%20the%20latest%20phase%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20sale%20that%20lasted%20from%20January%202%20to%20January%2011%2C%202024%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Felectoral-bonds-worth-more-than-rs-570-crore-sold-in-january-alone-60-in-the-value-of-rs-1-crore%5C%22%3Ehad%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20query%20filed%20by%20transparency%20activist%20Commodore%20Lokesh%20Batra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F2793520172024-02-15-522601.pdf%5C%22%3Ekey%20quotes%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20apex%20court%20on%20electoral%20bonds%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20and%20the%20impugned%20provisions%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20they%20infringe%20upon%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20the%20voter%20by%20anonymising%20contribution%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20are%20violative%20of%20Article%2019%20(1)(a)%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20CJI%2C%20as%20per%20a%20report%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F2793520172024-02-15-522601.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEconomic%20inequality%20leads%20to%20differing%20levels%20of%20political%20engagement%20because%20of%20the%20deep%20association%20between%20money%20and%20politics.%20At%20a%20primary%20level%2C%20political%20contributions%20give%20a%20%E2%80%9Cseat%20at%20the%20table%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20contributor.%20That%20is%2C%20it%20enhances%20access%20to%20legislators.%20This%20access%20also%20translates%20into%20influence%20over%20policymaking.%20An%20economically%20affluent%20person%20has%20a%20higher%20ability%20to%20make%20financial%20contributions%20to%20political%20parties%2C%20and%20there%20is%20a%20legitimate%20possibility%20that%20financial%20contribution%20to%20a%20political%20party%20would%20lead%20to%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangements%20because%20of%20the%20close%20nexus%20between%20money%20and%20politics.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInformation%20about%20political%20funding%20would%20enable%20a%20voter%20to%20assess%20if%20there%20is%20a%20correlation%20between%20policymaking%20and%20financial%20contributions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3EElectoral%20Bonds%20Are%20Illegal%20Now.%20But%20Who%20Benefitted%20for%20the%206%2B%20Years%20They%20Lasted%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20ability%20of%20a%20company%20to%20influence%20the%20electoral%20process%20through%20political%20contributions%20is%20much%20higher%20when%20compared%20to%20that%20of%20an%20individual.%20A%20company%20has%20a%20much%20graver%20influence%20on%20the%20political%20process%2C%20both%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20quantum%20of%20money%20contributed%20to%20political%20parties%20and%20the%20purpose%20of%20making%20such%20contributions.%20Contributions%20made%20by%20individuals%20have%20a%20degree%20of%20support%20or%20affiliation%20to%20a%20political%20association.%20However%2C%20contributions%20made%20by%20companies%20are%20purely%20business%20transactions%2C%20made%20with%20the%20intent%20of%20securing%20benefits%20in%20return.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20purpose%20of%20Section%20182%20is%20to%20curb%20corruption%20in%20electoral%20financing.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20purpose%20of%20banning%20a%20government%20company%20from%20contributing%20is%20to%20prevent%20such%20companies%20from%20entering%20into%20the%20political%20fray%20by%20making%20contributions%20to%20political%20parties.%20The%20amendment%20to%20Section%20182%20by%20permitting%20unlimited%20corporate%20contributions%20(including%20by%20shell%20companies)%20authorizes%20unrestrained%20influence%20of%20companies%20on%20the%20electoral%20process.%20This%20is%20violative%20of%20the%20principle%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20and%20political%20equality%20captured%20in%20the%20value%20of%20%E2%80%9Cone%20person%20one%20vote%E2%80%9D.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708011396000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-top-supreme-court-quotes%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Information%20about%20political%20funding%20would%20enable%20a%20voter%20to%20assess%20if%20there%20is%20a%20correlation%20between%20policymaking%20and%20financial%20contributions%2C'%20said%20the%20top%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-top-supreme-court-quotes%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Facing%20Challenges%20Today%20But%20No%20Need%20To%20Worry%3A%20Sharad%20Pawar%20To%20NCP%20Workers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ENCP%20founder%20Sharad%20Pawar%20said%20his%20party%20belonged%20to%20the%20common%20man%2C%20and%20although%20it%20was%20going%20through%20a%20difficult%20time%20today%2C%20nobody%20should%20worry%20about%20the%20challenges%20it%20was%20facing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20stressed%20there%20was%20a%20need%20to%20stay%20united%20and%20work%20towards%20improving%20the%20state's%20image.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Pawar%20was%20addressing%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20(Sharadchandra%20Pawar)%20group's%20convention%20of%20young%20women%20in%20Mumbai%20hours%20before%20Maharashtra%20assembly%20Speaker%20Rahul%20Narwekar%20passed%20his%20verdict%20on%20the%20disqualification%20of%20the%20rival%20NCP%20factions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Speaker%20held%20that%20the%20Ajit%20Pawar-led%20group%20was%20the%20real%20NCP%20when%20two%20factions%20emerged%20in%20July%202023%20and%20dismissed%20disqualification%20petitions%20filed%20by%20both%20factions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20function%2C%20Sharad%20Pawar%20said%20the%20decision%20to%20form%20the%20NCP%20was%20made%20in%20this%20same%20hall%2025%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20lakhs%20of%20party%20workers%20across%20the%20state%20came%20forward%20to%20support%20the%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20NCP%20is%20a%20party%20of%20the%20common%20people.%20Today%2C%20it%20is%20facing%20challenges%2C%20but%20you%20and%20I%20should%20not%20be%20worried%20about%20these%20challenges.%20We%20will%20stay%20united%20and%20make%20decisions%20that%20will%20benefit%20the%20next%20generation.%20We%20will%20work%20towards%20improving%20the%20state's%20image%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithin%20three%20months%20of%20NCP's%20formation%2C%20the%20people%20of%20the%20state%20entrusted%20the%20party%20with%20the%20responsibility%20of%20governing%20the%20state.%20Many%20young%20leaders%20from%20the%20party%20emerged%20as%20formidable%20forces%2C%20working%20to%20address%20the%20issues%20of%20common%20people%20in%20the%20state%20for%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%