01919%2C%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20wrote%20that%20the%20British%20regime%20perpetuated%20itself%20by%20employing%20the%20doctrine%20of%20frightfulness.%C2%A0%20It%20struck%20fear%20in%20the%20hearts%20of%20people%20who%C2%A0were%20expected%20to%20meekly%20surrender%20before%20the%20colonial%20authorities%20by%20accepting%20falsehoods%20spun%20by%20them%20and%20forsaking%20not%20just%20protest%20but%20even%20a%20questioning%20attitude%20either%20in%20public%20or%20through%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20doctrine%20of%20frightfulness%20is%20being%20replayed%20in%20the%20India%20of%202024.%20Those%20sections%20of%20the%20media%20which%20question%20the%20Modi%20regime%20are%20under%20attack%20and%20opposition%20parties%20are%20being%20split.%20People%E2%80%99s%20representatives%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20occupy%20high%20constitutional%20positions%2C%20are%20not%20spared.%20Many%20of%20them%20face%20jail%2C%20the%20threat%20of%20incarceration%20or%20repeated%20coercive%20action%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20government%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJail%20or%20BJP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2012%2C%20former%20Maharashtra%20Chief%20Minister%20Ashok%20Chavan%20and%20a%20veteran%20leader%20of%20%C2%A0Congress%20resigned%20from%20the%20party.%20He%20was%20facing%20several%20corruption%20cases.%20A%20day%20later%2C%20he%20joined%20the%20BJP.%20The%20political%20buzz%20is%20that%20he%20was%20told%20he%20had%20two%20options%20%E2%80%93%20join%20the%20BJP%20or%20go%20to%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20exemplifies%20how%20the%20doctrine%20of%20fear%20is%20used%20to%20actuate%20a%20former%20chief%20minister%20of%20a%20major%20state%20like%20Maharashtra%20to%20resign%20from%20his%20party%20and%20embrace%20the%20BJP.%20In%20Maharashtra%2C%20the%20%C2%A0opposition%20Shiv%20Sena%20and%20%C2%A0Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20were%20split%20as%20the%20doctrine%20of%20fear%20was%20invoked%20against%20key%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETargeting%20media%20With%20doctrine%20of%20frightfulness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20newspapers%20and%20independent%20media%20platforms%20such%20as%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENewsclick%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3ECaravan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%3Cem%3E%C2%A0The%20Wire%20and%20Newslaundry%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0have%20faced%20punitive%20action.%C2%A0In%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20press%20club%20was%20shut%20down%20and%20several%20journalists%20were%20jailed%20on%20trumped%20up%20charges.%20In%20the%20case%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENewsclick%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20its%20founding%20editor%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20faces%20terrorism%20charges%20under%20the%20draconian%20UAPA%20law%20for%20%C2%A0discharging%20journalistic%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Modi%20often%20takes%20pride%20in%20saying%20that%20India%20is%20the%20mother%20of%20democracy%20and%20yet%20his%20regime%20is%20acting%20contrary%20to%20basic%20democratic%20values.%20The%20relentless%20penal%20measures%20directed%20against%20the%20media%20flow%20from%20the%20doctrine%20of%20frightfulness%20which%20is%20applied%20with%20impunity%20to%20make%20independent%20and%20critical%20media%20subservient%20to%20the%20government%2C%20just%20as%20corporate%20media%20already%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20developments%20remind%20us%20of%20the%20dark%20days%20of%20martial%20law%20imposed%20in%20Punjab%20following%20the%20Jallianwala%20Bagh%20%C2%A0massacre%20and%20the%20suppression%20of%20the%20press.%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20in%20his%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fee01389b-a997-4247-ab9b-cc72b0069edb%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fee01389b-a997-4247-ab9b-cc72b0069edb%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1708081370779000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3yFvEX-FOOOFNgthCWnWHk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%20on%20the%20Punjab%20Disorders%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0observed%20that%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9CThe%20existence%20of%20independent%20journalism%20became%20an%20impossibility%20during%20the%20Martial%20Law%20regime%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Tribune%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EPunjabee%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EPratap%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0stopped%20publishing%E2%80%9D.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThose%20words%20of%20Gandhi%20resonate%20in%20India%20now%20when%20there%20is%20a%20great%20threat%20posed%20to%20independent%20journalism%20and%20those%20media%20platforms%20who%20dare%20to%20question%20the%20powers%20that%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGandhi%E2%80%99s%20prophetic%20observations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20days%20after%20drafting%C2%A0%E2%80%9CPunjab%20Disorder%E2%80%9D%20his%20Punjab%20report%2C%20%C2%A0Gandhi%2C%20in%20his%20speech%20delivered%20on%2023rd%20August%201920%20at%20Bezwada%2C%20stated%20that%20the%20British%20Government%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6does%20not%20scruple%20to%20use%20means%20fair%20or%20foul%20in%20order%20to%20gain%20its%20ends%E2%80%9D.%20As%20the%20massive%20crowd%20attentively%20listening%20to%20him%20cried%2C%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9CShame!%E2%80%9D%20he%20remarked%2C%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9CNo%20craft%20is%20above%20that%20Government%E2%80%9D.%20He%20then%20forcefully%20added%2C%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9CIt%20resorts%20to%20frightfulness%2C%20terrorism.%20It%20resorts%20to%20bribery%20in%20the%20shape%20of%20titles%2C%20honours%20and%20high%20offices%E2%80%9D.%20The%20crowd%20again%20cried%2C%20%E2%80%9CShame!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGandhi%E2%80%99s%20possibly%20would%20have%20used%20the%20words%2C%20%E2%80%9Cfrightfulness%2C%20terrorism%2C%E2%80%9D%20%C2%A0if%20he%20had%20been%20alive%20in%20the%20India%20of%202024.%20He%20charged%20that%20titles%2C%20honours%20and%20high%20offices%20offered%20by%20the%20British%20rulers%20amounted%20to%20%C2%A0bribery.%20In%20retrospect%20those%20words%20assume%20relevance%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20recent%20announcement%20of%20%C2%A0Bharat%20Ratnas%20for%20personalities%20such%20as%20Karpoori%20%C2%A0Thakur%2C%20L.K.%20Advani%2C%20Charan%20Singh%2C%20P.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%20and%20M.S.%20Swaminathan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20speech%2C%20Gandhi%20very%20critically%20observed%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20administers%20opiates%20in%20the%20form%20of%20reforms%E2%80%A6%20In%20any%20sense%20it%20is%20autocracy%20doubly%20distilled%2C%20appearing%20in%20the%20guise%20of%20democracy%20for%20the%20greatest%20gifts%20of%20a%20crafty%2C%20cunning%20man%20are%20worthless%20so%C2%A0%3Cspan%3Elong%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0as%20cunning%20resides%20in%20his%20heart%E2%80%9D.%20Very%20prescient%20articulations%20indeed!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGandhi%20was%20also%20clear%20about%20the%20message%20he%20had%20for%20the%20people.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CI%20have%20given%20to%20you%20these%20qualities%20of%20this%20Government%20not%20in%20order%20to%20excite%20your%20angry%20passions%20but%20in%20order%20that%20you%20may%20appreciate%20fully%20the%20forces%20that%20are%20matched%20against%20you%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CAnger%E2%80%9D%2C%20Gandhi%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20serve%20no%20purpose.%E2%80%9D%20He%20then%20firmly%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9C%20We%20shall%20have%20to%20meet%20their%20untruth%20by%20truth.%20We%20shall%20have%20to%20meet%20terrorism%2C%20their%20frightfulness%20by%20bravery%2C%20and%20it%20is%20an%20unbending%20bravery.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20now%20a%C2%A0replay%20of%20the%20doctrine%20of%20frightfulness%20and%20it%20is%20amply%20manifested%20in%20India.%20The%20assertion%20of%20Gandhi%20that%20truth%20has%20to%20be%20employed%20to%20counter%20untruth%20and%20terrorism%20and%20frightfulness%20by%20bravery%20and%2C%20that%20too%20unbending%20bravery%2C%20is%20surely%20a%20manifesto%20for%20our%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ES.N.%20Sahu%20served%20as%20Officer%20on%20Special%20Duty%20to%20President%20of%20India%20K.R.%20Narayanan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20updated%20and%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708003981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F30082243%2FIMG_1748.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgandhis-doctrine-of-frightfulness-british-modi-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Those%20sections%20of%20the%20media%20which%20question%20the%20Modi%20regime%20are%20under%20attack%20and%20opposition%20parties%20are%20being%20split.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgandhis-doctrine-of-frightfulness-british-modi-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98We%20Need%20a%20Politics%20Which%20Is%20Inclusive%2C%20Rather%20Than%20Exclusive%E2%80%99%3A%20What%20Manmohan%20Singh%20Said%20in%201999%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09154913%2FMMS-3.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Manmohan%20Singh%20is%20likely%20to%20retire%20from%20public%20life%2C%20we%20take%20a%20look%20at%20one%20of%20his%20interviews%2C%20conducted%20by%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%20%3C%2Fem%3EBBC%3Cem%3E%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ci%3EAugust%2025%2C%201999.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20this%20interview%2C%20Singh%20delved%20into%20his%20political%20values%20and%20perspectives%20on%20the%20state%20of%20affairs%20in%20India.%20He%20discussed%20his%20transition%20to%20contesting%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20emphasising%20the%20need%20for%20politics%20to%20serve%20social%20change.%20He%20addressed%20challenges%2C%20such%20as%20social%20division%20and%20economic%20mismanagement%2C%20while%20outlining%20his%20vision%20for%20reform.%20He%20also%20emphasised%20the%20importance%20of%20restoring%20politics%20as%20a%20moral%20instrument.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20full%20transcript%20of%20the%20interview%20is%20reproduced%20below.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHello%20and%20welcome%20to%20%E2%80%98Hardtalk%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20the%20second%20of%20three%20interviews%20with%20top%20leaders%20of%20the%C2%A0%20three%20parties%20contesting%20these%20elections.%20Today%20we%20talk%20to%20the%20man%20that%20many%20consider%20the%C2%A0%20likely%20choice%20for%20prime%20minister%20if%20the%20Congress%20party%20is%20in%20a%20position%20to%20form%20the%20next%C2%A0%20government.%20So%20what%20are%20his%20political%20values%2C%20and%20how%20does%20he%20view%20the%20present%20state%20of%C2%A0%20affairs%20in%20India%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Here%20to%20answer%20those%20questions%20is%20former%20finance%20minister%20and%20the%20present%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20%E2%80%93%20Dr.%20Manmohan%20Singh.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDr.%20Singh%2C%20after%20eight%20years%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20you%20have%20decided%20to%20stand%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20%E2%80%93%20something%20you%20consciously%20didn%E2%80%99t%20do%20in%201996%20and%20you%20didn%E2%80%99t%20do%20in%201998.%20What%20has%20brought%20about%20the%20change%20of%20mind%20this%20time%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20was%20initially%20very%20reluctant%20to%20contest%20this%20time%20also.%20But%20our%20party%20felt%20that%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20party%2C%20and%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20our%20country%2C%20it%20would%20be%20good%20if%20I%20offered%20myself%C2%A0%20for%20election.%20Although%20I%20have%20been%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20I%20do%20believe%20that%20the%20quality%20of%20membership%20that%20goes%20with%20the%20membership%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20is%20superior.%20Because%20you%20are%20elected%20directly%20by%20the%20people.%20Therefore%2C%20though%20I%20was%20initially%20reluctant%2C%20when%20I%20thought%20it%20over%2C%20I%20felt%3A%20I%20have%20been%20in%20politics%20now%20for%20eight%2C%20nine%20years%2C%20I%20should%20go%20to%20the%20people%20to%20pronounce%C2%A0%20their%20verdict%20on%20what%20I%20am%2C%20what%20I%20have%20been%20and%20what%20vision%2C%20what%20views%20I%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20in%20a%20sense%2C%20you%20are%20actually%20now%20seeking%20a%20mandate%20for%20the%20views%20you%20hold%E2%80%A6%20That%E2%80%99s%20true.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20think%2C%20however%2C%20that%20you%20are%20suited%20to%20this%20sort%20of%20electoral%20politics%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20had%20initial%20doubts%2C%20but%20I%20am%20learning%20very%20fast.%20And%20the%20last%20five%20or%20six%20days%20that%20I%20go%20campaigning%20every%20morning%2C%20every%20evening%20%E2%80%93%20I%20am%20finding%20it%20a%20very%20educational%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20me%20put%20something%20that%20people%20say%E2%80%A6%20Your%20admirers%20say%20that%20in%20stepping%20into%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20arena%2C%20Dr%20Manmohan%20Singh%20may%20be%20in%20danger%20of%20losing%20the%20one%20thing%20that%20made%20him%20different.%20Earlier%2C%20he%20was%20above%20politics%2C%20today%20in%20a%20sense%2C%20he%20is%20becoming%20a%20bit%20like%20any%20other%20politician%E2%80%A6%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20am%20in%20politics%20and%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20claim%20any%20special%20virtues.%20All%20I%20can%20say%20is%20that%20in%20politics%20I%C2%A0%20have%20learnt%20that%20one%20has%20to%20compromise.%20But%20there%20is%20a%20limit%20to%20compromise.%20If%20you%20compromise%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20your%20conscience%2C%20I%20think%20there%20you%20should%20draw%20the%20line.%20And%C2%A0whether%20I%20am%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20or%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20I%20hope%20I%20will%20have%20the%20moral%20courage%20to%20not%20cross%20that%20line.%20And%20that%20line%20is%20set%20by%20my%20own%20conscience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20will%20you%20still%20be%20able%20to%20do%20some%20of%20the%20things%20the%20country%20requires%2C%20speak%20out%20when%20you%20think%20the%20time%20has%20come%2C%20stand%20up%20for%20the%20views%20that%20you%20believe%20are%20correct%2C%20allow%20your%20voice%20to%20be%20heard%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20causes%20you%20have%20always%20supported%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20do%20believe%20we%20need%20a%20new%20type%20of%20politics.%20A%20politics%20of%20frankness%2C%20a%20politics%20that%20tells%20people%20things%20straight%2C%20things%20as%20they%20are.%20I%20think%20we%20cannot%20fool%20our%20people.%20As%20Abraham%20Lincoln%20once%20said%3A%20you%20can%20fool%20some%20people%20for%20all%20time%2C%20all%20people%20for%20some%20time%2C%20but%20not%20all%20people%20for%20all%20time.%20And%20I%20do%20believe%20that%20in%20the%20last%2050%20years%2C%20politicians%20have%20been%20taking%20our%20people%20for%20a%20ride.%20And%20I%20feel%20there%20is%20a%20great%20danger%20if%20the%20gap%20between%20what%20politicians%20say%2C%20promise%2C%20and%20what%20they%20do%2C%20grows%20the%20way%20it%20has%20been%20growing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20test%20that%20a%20little%2C%20Doctor%20Saab%2C%20because%20I%20think%20that%20in%20the%20seeds%20of%20that%20perhaps%20lie%20some%20of%20the%20hope%20for%20our%20country.%20Many%20people%20in%20India%20today%20feel%20a%20sense%20of%20alienation%2C%20a%20sense%20of%20disenchantment%20with%20Indian%20politics%20and%20Indian%20politicians.%20As%20a%20new%20man%20stepping%20into%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20arena%2C%20can%20you%20understand%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20do%20very%20much%20understand%20that%20politics%20in%20this%20country%20has%20to%20be%20the%20servant%20of%20social%20sympathy.%20It%20has%20to%20mediate%20among%20the%20societal%20tensions%20that%20are%20built%20into%20the%20body%20politic%20of%20a%20poor%20country%20trying%20to%20modernise%20itself.%20And%20you%20can%20do%20so%20only%20if%20people%20believe%20in%20your%20credentials.%20And%20if%20you%20are%20telling%20things%20and%20you%20have%20no%20intention%20of%20doing%20them%2C%20I%20think%20you%20are%20now%20trading%20on%20trust%2C%20and%20you%20cannot%20last%20very%20long%2C%20I%20think.%20people%20become%20cynical%20%E2%80%93%20alienated%2C%20as%20you%20put%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAs%20you%20say%2C%20telling%20the%20truth%20%E2%80%93%20even%20if%20it%20is%20the%20bitter%20truth%20%E2%80%93%20is%20very%20important.%20One%20of%20the%20fears%20that%20people%20of%20India%20have%20as%20they%20look%20at%20our%20quarreling%20politicians%2C%20our%20hung%20parliament%2C%20our%20divisions%20of%20race%2C%20creed%2C%20religion%2C%20language%20is%20that%20we%20could%20face%20%E2%80%93%20if%20things%20are%20not%20handled%20properly%20%E2%80%93%20disintegration.%20We%20could%20be%20poised%20at%20the%20brink%20of%20anarchy.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20have%20always%20felt%20that%20%E2%80%93%20if%20you%20read%20my%20speeches%20in%20parliament%2C%20I%20have%20warned%20the%20members%20of%20parliament%20%E2%80%93%20we%20should%20not%20assume%20there%20is%20a%20divine%20destiny%20which%20will%20ensure%20that%20India%20continues%20to%20flourish%20and%20prosper%20howsoever%20we%20mismanage%20our%20economy.%20Great%20nations%20like%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20have%20perished%2C%20they%20have%20disappeared%20from%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20earth.%20If%20the%20Indian%20polity%20is%20not%20well-managed%2C%20I%20think%20we%20ought%20to%20recognise%20that%20a%20similar%20danger%20can%20overtake%20us%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20we%20could%20collapse%2C%20like%20eastern%20European%20countries%20and%20the%20Soviet%20Union%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20not%20saying%20that%20that%20is%20on%20the%20cards%20right%20away%2C%20or%20that%20it%20is%20inevitable.%20But%20if%20we%20continue%20to%20mismanage%20our%20economy%2C%20if%20we%20continue%20to%20divide%20our%20country%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20religion%2C%20caste%20and%20other%20sectarian%20issues%2C%20I%20think%20there%20is%20a%20grave%20danger%20of%20that%20sort%20of%20thing%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20it%20is%20a%20serious%20thing%E2%80%A6%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20serious%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20me%20push%20that%20thought%20a%20little%20further%20for%20a%20moment.%20Many%20people%20feel%20that%20although%20we%20have%20considerable%20achievements%2C%20nonetheless%20the%20sense%20of%20purpose%20we%20had%2030%20years%20ago%20is%20lost.%20Today%2C%20moral%20authority%20is%20eroded%2C%20political%20authority%20is%20questioned.%20Do%20you%20think%20that%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Ethere%20is%20a%20danger%20that%20in%20fact%20that%20we%20could%20end%20up%20fragmenting%20the%20nation%20state%20that%20we%20have%3F%C2%A0%20Could%20%5Bthat%5D%20be%20in%20danger%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitics%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20has%20ceased%20to%20be%20%E2%80%93%20in%20many%20ways%20%E2%80%93%20a%20vehicle%20of%20purposeful%20social%20change.%20It%20has%20become%20a%20ticket%20for%20power%3A%20power%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20power%3B%20not%20power%20as%20an%20instrument%20of%20doing%20something%20good%20for%20society.%20And%20that%20is%2C%20I%20feel%2C%20a%20great%20source%20of%20anxiety%20and%20danger%20for%20the%20future%20of%20our%20polity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20has%20politics%20become%20a%20vehicle%20for%20self-serving%20politicians%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20means%20for%20change%20or%20a%20means%20for%20reform%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20I%20think%20that%20is%20very%20much%20true%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20that%20one%20reason%20why%20you%20have%20consciously%20decided%20to%20step%20into%20the%20arena%20and%20try%20to%20change%20things%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20have%20an%20opportunity%2C%20I%20do%20hope%20I%20will%2C%20I%20think%2C%20%5BI%E2%80%99ll%5D%20be%20a%20small%20instrument%20of%20writing%20some%20new%20guidelines%20for%20the%20way%20political%20processes%20should%20be%20conducted%20in%20our%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fv7e9kuJXfqQ%3Fsi%3DkZFvtxSXancXM-28%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20much%20of%20the%20crisis%20our%20country%20faces%20is%20also%20a%20result%20of%20another%20crisis%20%E2%80%93%20a%20crisis%20of%20leadership%3F%20To%20what%20extent%20have%20our%20leaders%2C%20historically%20and%20even%20today%2C%20let%20us%20down%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeadership%20is%20the%20crux%20of%20the%20matter.%20Look%20at%20China.%20After%20the%20disastrous%20results%20of%20the%20cultural%20revolution%2C%20there%20came%20the%20grand%20old%20man%2C%20Deng%20Xiaoping%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%2080%20years.%20And%20he%20transformed%20the%20Chinese%20society%20beyond%20recognition.%20Leaders%20have%20to%20be%20leaders%2C%20they%20have%20to%20be%20pace%20setters%2C%20not%20leaders%20who%20just%20follow%20what%20is%20momentarily%20in%20the%20popular%20mind%2C%20look%20at%20the%20opinion%20polls%20every%20day%20and%20adjust%20their%20thinking%20to%20that.%20I%20once%20said%20in%20parliament%20about%20leadership%2C%20quoting%20a%20couplet%3A%20%3Ci%3EInsaan%20voh%20nahin%20hai%20jo%20hava%20ke%20saath%20badle%2C%20insann%20toh%20vohi%20hai%20jo%20hava%20ka%20rukh%20badal%20de%20%3C%2Fi%3E%5B%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EMan%20is%20not%20the%20one%20who%20changes%20with%20the%20wind%3B%20man%20is%20the%20one%20who%20changes%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20wind.%5D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20think%20that%20we%20need%20leadership%20of%20that%20kind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDr.%20Singh%2C%20the%20hallmark%20of%20leaders%20whom%20you%20admire%20was%20their%20conviction.%20It%20was%20their%20strength%20of%20belief%20in%20what%20they%20wanted%20to%20do%20that%20gave%20them%20courage.%20Do%20you%2C%20therefore%2C%20believe%20that%20what%20we%20need%20today%20is%20conviction-based%20leadership%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20measure%20of%20strong%20conviction%2C%20Indian%20leadership%20cannot%20deliver%20the%20goods.%20And%20I%20say%20this%20in%20all%20sincerity%2C%20because%20at%20the%20present%20time%2C%20the%20aspirations%20of%20our%20people%20are%20rather%20modest.%20And%20if%20they%20have%20a%20leadership%20which%20is%20not%20sincere%2C%20which%20is%20not%20intent%2C%20which%C2%A0%20does%20not%20think%20how%20we%20all%20should%20work%20to%20meet%20those%20aspirations%2C%20then%20I%20think%2C%20tomorrow%2C%20it%20will%20be%20too%20late.%20The%20gap%20between%20aspirations%20and%20what%20is%20feasible%20%E2%80%93%20politically%2C%20economically%2C%20socially%20%E2%80%93%20will%20grow%20to%20a%20point%20that%20I%20think%20there%20will%20be%20a%20great%20danger%20of%20acute%20political%20stability%20in%20our%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20is%20it%20a%20question%20of%20now%20or%20never%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20very%20much%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20are%20on%20record%20as%20saying%20that%20what%20we%20need%20in%20our%20country%20is%20reform%20with%20big%20%E2%80%98R%E2%80%99%20in%20every%20sphere%2C%20but%20you%E2%80%99ve%20added%20that%20the%20political%20mindset%20of%20our%20politicians%20does%20not%20recognise%20this.%20Where%20do%20they%20fall%20short%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20politicians%20in%20our%20country%20do%20not%20adjust%20their%20thinking%20to%20the%20changing%20needs%20of%20our%20time.%20When%20I%20was%20a%20student%20at%20Nuffield%20College%2C%20Oxford%2C%20nearly%2040%20years%20ago%2C%20one%20of%20the%20persons%20who%20later%20became%20prime%20minister%20%E2%80%93%20James%20Callaghan%20%E2%80%93%20when%20he%20became%20the%20shadow%20chancellor%20of%20the%20exchequer%2C%20spent%20full%20one%20year%20at%20Nuffield%20College%2C%20taking%20tutorials%20in%20economics.%20He%20said%3A%20I%20could%20not%20function%20as%20an%20effective%20shadow%20chancellor%20unless%20I%20had%20a%20deep%20understanding%20of%20modern%20economic%20analysis.%20Our%20politicians%20feel%20that%20whatever%20they%20learnt%20in%20their%20childhood%20is%20adequate%20stock%20for%20them%20to%20pronounce%20on%20everything%20in%20the%20world.%20I%20think%20there%20is%20contempt%20for%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Raj%20Krishna%20once%20said%20that%20Indian%20politicians%20are%20knowledge-free.%20And%20we%20live%20in%20a%20world%20where%20knowledge%20is%20power.%20So%20unless%20those%20politicians%20value%20knowledge%2C%20I%20think%20they%20cannot%20be%20a%20purposeful%20instrument%20of%20social%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20also%20once%20said%20that%20international%20ideas%20of%20what%20constitute%20good%20policy%20are%20totally%20at%20variance%20with%20what%20our%20politicians%20think.%20Now%2C%20I%20think%20I%20understand%20what%20you%20are%20saying%2C%20but%20could%20you%20exemplify%20that%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20was%20talking%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20management%20of%20the%20economy.%20In%20the%201950%2C%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20commanding%20heights%20of%20the%20economy%20must%20rest%20with%20the%20public%20sector%3B%20that%20if%20you%20nationalise%20an%20industry%2C%20you%20contribute%20to%20growth%20as%20well%20as%20to%20growth%20with%20social%20justice%3B%20if%20you%20restrict%20private%20investment%20that%20also%20brings%20about%20socialism%3B%20if%20you%20raise%20tax%20rates%2C%20that%20helps%20to%20reduce%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20in%20all%20these%20matters%2C%20experience%20has%20shown%20that%20short-term%20solutions%20%5Bare%20inadequate%5D.%20As%20Alfred%20Marshall%20taught%20at%20Cambridge%20many%20years%20ago%2C%20all%20short-term%20solutions%20have%20their%20limitations%20in%20social%20matters.%20Therefore%2C%20one%20has%20to%20change%20one%E2%80%99s%20thinking.%20The%20collapse%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20serves%20as%20a%20compelling%20example%20of%20why%20a%20command%20economy%20simply%20broke%20down.%20However%2C%20ideas%20associated%20with%20a%20command%20economy%20persist%20in%20the%20thinking%20of%20many%20of%20our%20politicians%20even%20to%20this%20day.%20The%20world%20has%20changed%2C%20and%20if%20we%20do%20not%20change%20our%20thinking%20in%20accordance%20to%20the%20changing%20needs%20of%20time%2C%20we%20%5Brisk%20being%20stuck%20with%5D%20have%20a%20Bradshaw%2C%20a%20railway%20timetable%20that%20is%20thoroughly%20outdated.%20And%20as%20a%20result%2C%20we%20may%20suddenly%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20are%20saying%20something%20more%E2%80%A6you%20are%20saying%20that%20our%20politicians%20are%20prisoners%20of%20failed%C2%A0%20truths%E2%80%A6%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%2C%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20true%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20fact%2C%20you%20are%20also%20implying%20that%20we%20have%20a%20dinosaur%20mentality%2C%20and%20we%20are%20in%20danger%20of%20the%20same%20fate%20that%20the%20dinosaurs%20met.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20there%20is%20indeed%20a%20danger%2C%20and%20I%20really%20believe%20it.%20How%20else%20can%20we%20explain%20the%20situation%20in%20this%20country%20where%20people%20can%20get%20votes%20based%20on%20religion%3F%20%5BHow%20is%20it%20that%20individuals%5D%20seek%20votes%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20caste%2C%20even%2050%20years%20after%20India%20adopted%20a%20constitution%20that%20talks%20about%20a%20classless%20society%3F%20Yet%2C%2050%20years%20later%2C%20we%20find%20Indian%20society%20is%20so%20badly%20divided%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20religion%20and%20caste.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDr.%20Singh%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20not%20only%20saying%20that%20we%20are%20prisoners%20of%20failed%20truths%2C%20but%20you%E2%80%99re%20also%20emphasising%20that%20we%20not%20only%20fail%20to%20realise%20this%20but%20are%20actually%20proud%20of%20our%20folly.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20politicians%2C%20I%20am%20sad%20to%20say%2C%20practice%20a%20very%20divisive%20politics%20for%20narrow%20sectarian%20reasons.%20It%20may%20be%20good%20politics%20for%20the%20moment%2C%20but%20it%20can%20be%20a%20source%20of%20disaster%20for%20our%20country.%20We%20need%20a%20type%20of%20politics%20which%20is%20inclusive%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20type%20of%20politics%20which%20is%20exclusive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20today%20sitting%20before%20me%2C%20you%20are%20calling%20for%20far-reaching%2C%20I%20might%20even%20call%20it%2C%20dramatic%20reform%20and%20changes%20in%20the%20way%20we%20operate.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20talking%20about%20change%20in%20the%20mindsets.%20I%20think%20institutional%20changes%20are%20necessary%2C%20but%20more%20than%20institutional%20change%20we%20need%20a%20change%20in%20mindsets.%20Of%20all%20those%20people%20who%20make%20critical%20decisions%20of%20our%20national%20life%20%E2%80%93%20be%20it%20in%20politics%2C%20be%20it%20in%20economics%2C%20be%20it%20in%20social%20engineering%20%E2%80%93%20we%20need%20a%20deep%20change%20in%20the%20mindsets%20of%20our%20people%2C%20in%20their%20thinking%2C%20at%20all%20levels.%20And%20more%20so%20in%20the%20mindsets%20of%20those%20who%20constitute%20our%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDr.%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%20that%20%5Bstatement%5D%20is%20not%20just%20forthright%3B%20many%20would%20say%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20stinging%20indictment%20of%20the%20political%20system%20as%20it%20exists%20today.%20I%20have%20to%20ask%20you%2C%20this%20is%20so%20different%20from%20the%20perception%20we%20have%20of%20the%20Congress%20party.%20Where%20do%20you%20fit%20in%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20came%20into%20politics%20by%20accident.%20I%20have%20stayed%20committed%20to%20the%20Congress%20party.%20And%20I%20do%20believe%20that%20there%20is%20a%20ray%20of%20hope.%20At%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fwhy-congress-wants-to-revisit-lessons-from-pachmarhi-shimla-7131550%2F%5C%22%3EPachmarhi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20of%20these%20issues%20were%20discussed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20forgotten%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20would%20not%20say%20forgotten.%20I%20think%20there%20are%20momentary%20lapses.%20Politicians%2C%20before%20they%20become%20statesmen%2C%20want%20to%20be%20re-elected.%20And%20when%20electoral%20compulsions%20come%2C%20people%20do%20make%20compromises.%20But%20I%20have%20faith%20in%20the%20power%20of%20ideas.%20As%20Victor%20Hugo%20once%20said%2C%20no%20power%20on%20earth%20can%20stop%20an%20idea%20whose%20time%20has%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20really%20believe%20that%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20is%20capable%20of%20representing%20the%20sort%20of%20dynamic%2C%20forward%20thinking%2C%20far-reaching%20change%20that%20you%20are%20calling%20for%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESonia%20ji%20is%20a%20very%20dynamic%20person.%20Whenever%20I%20have%20conversed%20with%20her%2C%C2%A0%20she%20is%20acutely%20conscious%20of%20the%20moral%20imperatives%2C%20the%20moral%20foundations%20of%20our%20polity%2C%20more%20than%20many%20other%20politicians%20in%20this%20country.%20She%20has%20in%20many%20discussions%20with%20me%20mentioned%20some%20of%20the%20problems%20which%20I%20have%20mentioned.%20How%20politics%20has%20ceased%20in%20our%20country%20to%20be%20a%20purposeful%20instrument%20of%20social%20change.%20How%20we%20are%20all%20bereft%20of%20all%20the%20morals%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMay%20I%20interrupt%20you%20for%20a%20minute%20%E2%80%93%20her%20appeal%20is%20emotional%20and%20passion-driven%2C%20yours%20is%20one%20of%20logic%20and%20reason.%20Where%20do%20the%20two%20of%20you%20meet%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20a%20small%20entity%20in%20the%20Congress%20party.%20And%20Sonia%20ji%20is%20the%20acknowledged%20leader%20of%20the%20Congress%20party.%20She%20was%20elected%20leader%20of%20our%20party%20at%20a%20time%20when%20our%20party%20was%20in%20deep%20crisis.%20And%20that%20she%20sways%20the%20minds%20and%20hearts%20of%20our%20party%20was%20certainly%20displayed%20in%20May%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20%5Bdoes%5D%20she%20provide%20the%20vote-winning%20edge%3F%20%5BAnd%5D%20would%20you%2C%20in%20a%20sense%2C%20be%20the%20moral%2C%20principled%20backbone%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20not%20the%20only%20one%2C%20I%20am%20only%20a%20small%20entity%20in%20this%20large%20organisation%20called%20the%20Congress%20party.%20I%20am%20not%20saying%20that%20I%20have%20the%20monopoly%20of%20virtue%2C%20or%20that%20I%20am%20the%20only%20one%20who%20knows%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20you%20are%20the%20strongest%2C%20clearest%20voice%20today%20calling%20for%20reform%20and%20change.%20The%20strongest%20voice%20pointing%20out%20that%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20correct%20ourselves%2C%20we%20may%20lose%20the%20opportunity%20to%20forever%20do%20so.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20young%20people%20in%20our%20party%20who%20feel%20the%20same%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20opportunity%20and%20advantage%20that%20you%20have%20today%2C%20of%20being%20a%20frontline%20leader.%20You%20are%20for%20them%20the%20first%20person%20in%20the%20line.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20do%20not%20know%20what%20line%20you%20are%20talking%20about.%20As%20I%20said%2C%20now%20I%20am%20only%20seeking%20election%20to%20the%20membership%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20All%20the%20rest%20is%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20speculation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsolutely%2C%20and%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20embarrass%20you%20by%20forcing%20you%20to%20make%20modest%20disclaimers%20about%20what%20will%20happen%20after%20the%20elections.%20Let%20me%20ask%20a%20hypothetical%20question%20instead.%20If%20you%20were%20to%20be%20the%20head%20of%20the%20government%20after%20the%20elections%2C%20do%20you%20think%20you%20would%20be%20capable%20of%C2%A0%20pushing%20through%20the%20far-reaching%20reforms%20that%20you%20are%20talking%20about%2C%20in%20a%20constructive%2C%20cohesive%2C%20proper%2C%20forceful%20way%3F%20Or%20would%20it%20be%20piecemeal%2C%20would%20it%20be%20one%20step%20forward%2C%20one%20step%20back%3F%20Would%20it%20be%20ad%20hoc%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20me%20say%20who%20will%20head%20the%20government%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%20a%20hypothetical%20question.%20We%20will%20cross%20that%20bridge%20when%20we%20reach%20there.%20But%20I%20sincerely%20believe%20that%20whosoever%20is%20the%20head%20of%20the%C2%A0%20government%2C%20ought%20to%20implement%20a%20coherent%20programme%20of%20action%20if%20our%20country%20has%20to%20move%20in%20the%20desired%20direction%20in%20the%20desired%20way.%20We%20cannot%20have%20a%20system%20%E2%80%93%20as%20my%20esteemed%20friend%20P.N.%20Dhar%20used%20to%20say%3A%20in%20this%20country%2C%20we%20can%20have%20growth%20only%20through%20stealth%2C%20we%20cannot%20do%20it%20the%20straight%20way.%20I%20think%20that%20time%20is%20over.%20We%20must%20do%20things%20the%20straight%20way%2C%20tell%20our%20people%20what%20are%20the%20options%2C%20what%20are%20the%20costs%2C%20what%20are%20the%20benefits%20and%20then%20tell%20them%20why%20we%20consider%2C%20on%20balance%2C%20a%20particular%20course%20of%20action%20is%20the%C2%A0%20best%20%5Bchoice%20overall%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELevel%20with%20Indians%2C%20to%20tell%20them%20the%20truth%20as%20you%20see%20it%2C%20and%20if%20it%20is%20bitter%2C%20then%20it%20is%20bitter.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20think%20that%20we%20cannot%20carry%20forward%20the%20social%20and%20economic%20transformation%20that%20our%20country%20needs%20to%20realise%20the%20vision%20of%20the%20founding%20fathers%20of%20our%20republic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESuch%20as%20the%20financial%2C%20because%20you%20also%20have%20to%20sell%20to%20them%20the%20essential%20message%20that%20we%20must%20learn%20to%20live%20within%20our%20means%2C%20that%20we%20have%20to%20tighten%20our%20belts%20today%20for%20a%20better%20tomorrow.%20And%20those%20sometimes%20are%20difficult%20things%20to%20say.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20difficult.%20And%20I%20often%20used%20to%20say%20in%20my%20budget%20speeches%20that%20money%20does%20not%C2%A0%20grow%20on%20trees.%20And%20therefore%2C%20I%20think%20there%20is%20such%20a%20thing%20as%20resource%20constraint.%20If%20there%20were%20no%20resource%20constraints%2C%20then%20money%20could%20be%20simply%20printed%20for%20all%20purposes.%20Every%20society%20would%20be%20a%20rich%20society%20today.%20The%20fact%20that%20most%20of%20the%20countries%20are%20poor%20is%20because%20of%20a%20shortage%20of%20resources.%20So%2C%20you%20are%2C%20therefore%2C%20correct%20that%20a%20political%20or%20economic%20leadership%2C%20which%20tells%20the%20people%20that%20there%20is%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20a%20resource%20constraint%2C%20%5Bcan%20lead%20to%5D%20this%20is%20a%20concept%20of%20disaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20is%20also%20a%20political%20leadership%20of%20lying%E2%80%A6%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20it%20is%20lying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20the%20challenge%20of%20telling%20the%20people%20the%20truth%20that%20you%20are%20going%20to%20face.%20Should%C2%A0%20you%20happen%20to%20be%20in%20that%20position%20%E2%80%93%20the%20other%20challenge%20is%20of%20convincing%20the%20Congress%20party%20that%20the%20reform%2C%20that%20the%20change%20in%20the%20mindsets%2C%20that%20telling%20the%20people%20the%20truth%20even%20if%20it%20is%20bitter%2C%20even%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20popularity%20has%20to%20be%20done.%20Can%20you%20carry%20your%20party%20with%20you%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20let%20me%20say%2C%20if%20you%20read%20our%20election%20manifesto%E2%80%A6.%20People%20have%20compared%20the%20Bharaiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20or%20the%20so-called%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20manifesto%20and%20our%20manifesto.%20I%20think%20most%20people%20will%20say%20that%20we%20have%20spelt%20out%20%5Bour%20agenda%5D%20far%20more%20clearly%20than%20the%20BJP%20has%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20me%20say%2C%20we%20have%2C%20I%20think%2C%20spelt%20out%20these%20things%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20great%20detail%20%E2%80%93%20sector-%20wise.%20Where%20our%20system%20is%20really%20weak%20is%20about%20bringing%20about%20a%20fiscal%20correction.%20There%20%5Bin%20that%20aspect%5D%20all%20political%20parties%2C%20I%20think%2C%20suffer%20from%20a%20lack%20of%20vision%2C%20a%20sense%20of%20purpose%2C%20and%20a%20lack%20of%C2%A0%20adequate%20commitment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20do%20you%20believe%20you%E2%80%99re%20in%20a%20position%20to%20put%20fiscal%20correction%20back%20on%20the%20table%2C%20pursuing%20it%20doggedly%2C%20even%20if%20it%20makes%20you%20unpopular%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELook%20at%20my%20record.%20In%201991-92%2C%20when%20this%20country%20was%20in%20a%20desperate%20economic%20situation%2C%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20collapse%2C%20I%20came%20up%20with%20a%20budget%20which%20cut%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20in%20a%20single%20year%20%E2%80%93%20in%20fact%20in%20eight%20or%20nine%20months%20%E2%80%93%20by%202%25%20of%20the%20GDP.%20We%20slashed%20subsidies%20all%20round.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20what%20happened%20after%20Babri%20Masjid%E2%80%A6%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20%5Bevent%5D%2C%20the%20political%20agenda%20overtook%20the%20economic%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMight%20that%20not%20happen%20again%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20cannot%20say%20that%20events%20will%20not%20overtake%E2%80%A6%20I%20think%20you%20cannot%20predict%20social%20evolution.%20The%20process%20of%20social%20evolution%20is%20never%20a%20linear%20process.%20I%20think%20exogenous%20events%20sometimes%20derail%20the%20process.%20It%20has%20happened%20before%2C%20it%20may%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20will%20your%20personal%20determination%20to%20stay%20on%20course%20always%20be%20there%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course.%20If%20I%20have%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20managing%20our%20economy%20and%20polity%2C%20we%20will%20try%20to%20erect%20safeguards%20that%20will%20not%20derail%20the%20inherent%20rhythm%20of%20the%20reform%20process%20that%20our%20country%20needs%20to%20realise%20the%20vision%20of%20our%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJust%20a%20couple%20of%20points%E2%80%A6%20If%20you%20were%20to%20be%20in%20charge%20in%20the%20next%20government%2C%20would%20you%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20continue%20with%20fairly%20sizable%20and%20dramatic%20disinvestment%20so%20that%20the%20state%20is%20freed%20from%20tasks%20it%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20doing%2C%20and%20concentrate%20on%20areas%20where%20it%20is%20needed%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20do%20want%20privatization%2C%20but%20not%20privatization%20all%20along%20the%20line.%20We%20believe%20that%20where%20public%20sector%20enterprises%20are%20running%20efficiently%2C%20there%20is%20no%20reason%20to%20privatise%20them.%20But%20the%20public%20sector%20has%20no%20business%20to%20be%20in%20hotels%20or%20other%20low%20priority%20activities%2C%20so%20we%20will%20get%20them%20out%20of%20those.%20And%20the%20resources%20that%20we%20save%2C%20we%20will%20put%20in%20education%2C%20health%2C%20and%20in%20areas%20we%20feel%20the%20state%20ought%20to%20be%20more%20actively%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20about%20government%20expenditure%3F%20Would%20you%20be%20able%20to%20curb%20it%20from%20running%20away%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20cannot%20be%20curbed%20overnight.%20We%20need%20a%20perspective%20of%20three%20to%20four%20years%20to%20bring%20about%20an%20orderly%20adjustment%20of%20government%20expenditure.%20We%20will%20work%20to%20that%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20will%20you%20rigidly%20stick%20to%20that%20purpose%3F%20You%20won%E2%80%99t%20let%20yourself%20be%20blown%20off%20course%20by%20adverse%20reaction%20or%20unpopularity%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20I%20think%20we%20would%20make%20every%20effort%20to%20ensure%20that%20expenditure%20aligns%20with%20broadly%20agreed-upon%20national%20priorities%3B%20that%20the%20overall%20government%20expenditure%20pattern%20conforms%20to%20national%20priorities%3B%20and%20that%20the%20level%20of%20expenditure%20remains%20consistent%20with%20the%20limits%20of%20fiscal%20prudence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20you%20scale%20the%20government%20down%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20will%20do%20that.%20I%20think%20the%20government%20is%20too%20bloated.%20I%20think%20areas%20that%20the%20government%20has%20no%C2%A0%20business%20to%20be%20in%E2%80%A6%20I%20think%20there%20are%20far%20too%20many%20ministries%20in%20the%20central%20government.%20Now%20we%20do%20not%20want%20to%20create%2C%20overnight%2C%20unnecessary%20unemployment%20in%20the%20public%20sector%2C%20but%20over%C2%A0%20a%20period%20of%20time%2C%20we%20must%20restructure%20our%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20last%20question%20Dr.%20Singh%3A%20you%20have%20sketched%20out%20a%20very%20effective%20agenda%20for%20reform.%20You%20have%20committed%20yourself%20to%20the%20need%20for%20conviction%20for%20change.%20The%20major%20question%20people%20want%20to%20know%20is%2C%20will%20your%20party%20agree%20to%20this%3F%20Or%20whether%20it%20will%20have%20the%20courage%20to%20persist%20with%20it.%20But%20let%20me%20ask%20a%20personal%20question%3A%20Should%20you%20lose%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%2C%20will%20you%20throw%20in%20the%20towel%2C%20or%20would%20you%20continue%20to%20fight%20%E2%80%93%20in%20some%20other%20way%20%E2%80%93%20for%20what%20you%20believe%20in%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20there%20is%20no%20question%20of%20throwing%20in%20the%20towel.%20I%20am%20in%20the%20fray.%20I%20am%20in%20politics.%20And%20my%20politics%20does%20not%20end%20with%20winning%20or%20losing%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%20I%20have%20come%20to%20politics%20in%20the%20belief%20that%20we%20must%20restore%20politics%20to%20its%20original%20purpose%20of%20being%20a%20purposeful%C2%A0%20instrument%20of%20social%20change%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20a%20moral%20instrument.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20a%20moral%20instrument.%20Ultimately%20our%20politics%20must%20be%20rooted%20%E2%80%93%20as%20Gandhi%20ji%20used%20to%20say%20%E2%80%93%20in%20fundamental%20human%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%5BSince%5D%20you%20mentioned%20Gandhi%20ji%2C%20if%20you%20happen%20to%20lose%2C%20will%20you%20continue%20as%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20or%20will%20you%20feel%20the%20moral%20compunction%20to%20step%20down%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20do%20feel%20that%20I%20will%20have%20the%20moral%20compunction%E2%80%A6%20In%20that%20situation%2C%20probably%2C%20it%20would%20be%20wise%20for%20me%20not%20to%20stay%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20if%20we%20are%20in%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEven%20if%20your%20party%20insists%2C%20will%20you%20step%20down%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20that%20is%20my%20intention.%20If%20I%20lose%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20%E2%80%93%20having%20gone%20to%20the%20people%2C%20not%20having%20won%20their%20verdict%2C%20and%20then%20still%20staying%20in%20power%20as%20leader%20of%20my%20party%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20I%20think%20that%20probably%20will%20not%20be%20a%20desirable%20course%20of%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDr%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%20many%20would%20hope%20that%20that%20does%20not%20come%20to%20pass.%20Obviously%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20something%20for%20me%20to%20comment%20on.%20Thank%20you%20very%20much%20for%20talking%20so%20openly%20and%20so%20frankly.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThank%20you%20very%20much%2C%20Karan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThank%20you%2C%20sir.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fv7e9kuJXfqQ%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Hardtalk%20India%20Manmohan%20Singh%2025%208%201999%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranscribed%20by%20Daman%20%3Cspan%3ESingh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708003844000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09154913%2FMMS-3.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwe-need-a-politics-which-is-inclusive-rather-than-exclusive-what-manmohan-singh-said-in-1999%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'We%20need%20a%20deep%20change%20in%20the%20mindsets%20of%20our%20people%2C%20in