0of%20mountains.%20Great%20impacts%20injected%20new%20material%20into%20our%20planet%2C%20cracking%20and%20reshaping%20its%20biogeochemistry.%20In%20this%20environment%2C%20about%203.5%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20some%20of%20those%20early%20cells%20evolved%20a%20new%20ability%20to%20convert%20light-energy%20from%20the%20sun%20into%20chemical%20fuel%20through%20a%20process%2C%20called%20%3Cem%3Ephotosynthesis%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20takes%20carbon-dioxide%20from%20the%20air%20and%20emits%20oxygen%20as%20metabolic%20waste.%20By%20two%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20buildup%20of%20oxygen%20was%20turning%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20skies%20blue%20above%20its%20oceans%20of%20rust-red.%20Many%20forms%20of%20life%20in%20that%20nascent%20biosphere%20were%20poisoned%20by%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fslate.com%2Ftechnology%2F2014%2F07%2Fthe-great-oxygenation-event-the-earths-first-mass-extinction.html%5C%22%3Eatmospheric%20oxygen%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20went%20extinct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3ECoal%20beds%20found%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mlsu.ac.in%2Fecontents%2F1895_Distribution%252520of%252520Coal%252520%26amp%3B%252520Petroleum%252520in%252520India.pdf%5C%22%3Epeninsular%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20the%20remains%20of%20swamp%20forests%20that%20bloomed%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffossil.energy.gov%2Finternational%2FPublications%2Fucg_1106_gsi.pdf%5C%22%3E290%20million%20years%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20supercontinent%20Pangea%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2F38218-facts-about-pangaea.html%5C%22%3Ein%20extreme%20southern%20latitudes%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20Earth%20was%20so%20hot%20that%20forests%20bloomed%20near%20Antarctica.%20But%20170%20million%20years%20later%2C%20the%20land%20containing%20those%20primeval%20forests%E2%80%94long%20since%20dead%20and%20buried%E2%80%94broke%20off%20as%20an%20island%20and%20floated%20northward.%20Its%20collision%20with%20the%20Eurasian%20landmass%