rishak%20Samman%20Award%20by%20the%20Maharana%20Pratap%20University%20of%20Agriculture%20and%20Technology%2C%20and%20the%20Krishithon%20Innovative%20Young%20Farmer%20award%20for%20innovative%20fruit%20farming%20and%20multi-fruit%20crop%20pattern%20by%20Krishithon%20%E2%80%93%20India%E2%80%99s%20premier%20agriculture%20trade%20fair%20in%20Nashik.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%20at%20his%20success%2C%20he%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CToday%E2%80%99s%20generation%20looks%20at%20agriculture%20as%20a%20loss-making%20sector.%20With%20my%20example%2C%20I%20want%20to%20showcase%20that%20agriculture%20can%20be%20turned%20into%20a%20good%20business%20opportunity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20need%20the%20younger%20generation%20in%20farming%20so%20that%20they%20can%20turn%20agriculture%20profitable%20by%20adopting%20new%20technologies%20over%20conventional%20methods%20because%20of%20their%20wit%20and%20skills.%20It%20was%20because%20of%20my%20education%20that%20I%20used%20social%20media%20and%20visited%20many%20countries%20like%20Thailand%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20and%20Israel%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20challenges%20in%20farming%20and%20progress.%20This%20would%20not%20have%20been%20expected%20from%20the%20older%20generations%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EAll%20photos%3A%20Mahesh%20Asabe.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707801328000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D341533%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20a%20time%20when%20dragon%20fruit%20was%20not%20popular%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20Mahesh%20Asabe%20set%20up%20a%20profitable%20business%20with%20dragon%20fruit%20cultivation.%20Today%2C%20he%20leads%20the%20way%20by%20earning%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20per%20acre%20in%20the%20water-scarce%20Solapur%20district.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F341533%2Fdragon-fruit-farming-in-solapur-drought-maharashtra-mahesh-asabe-rukmini-farms-earns-crores%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IIT%20Professor%E2%80%99s%20Novel%20Technique%20Produces%20High-Quality%20Vermicompost%20in%20Half%20The%20Time%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EResearchers%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F333216%2Fiit-guwahati-invents-sensor-for-diabetes-diet-low-glycemic-index-food%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIIT-Guwahati%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20developed%20a%20novel%20two-stage%20biodegradation%20technique.%20This%20can%20not%20only%20help%20municipal%20corporations%20and%20other%20governing%20bodies%20to%20manage%20organic%20waste%20in%20an%20eco-friendly%20manner%2C%20but%20also%20generate%20quality%20vermicompost%20and%20organic%20compost%20with%20high%20NPK%20(nitrogen%2C%20phosphorus%2C%20and%20potassium)%20value%20and%20other%20micronutrients%20for%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELed%20by%20Dr%20Ajay%20S%20Kalamdhad%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20civil%20engineering%20at%20IIT-Guwahati%2C%20researchers%20under%20the%20institute%E2%80%99s%20Waste%20Management%20Research%20Group%20(WMRG)%20have%20devised%20an%20efficient%20and%20environmentally-friendly%20technique%2C%20which%20combines%20Rotary%20Drum%20Composting%20with%20Vermicomposting%20(RDVC).%20This%20novel%20technique%2C%20the%20institute%20claims%2C%20minimises%20biodegradation%20time%2C%20yields%20vermicompost%20with%204.2%25%20total%20nitrogen%20in%2027%20days%20(as%20compared%20to%20the%20standard%2045%20to%2060%20days)%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F339577%2Fhyderabad-abhishek-agarwal-goodeebag-free-waste-recycling-service%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eurban%20waste%20management%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20reduces%20the%20volume%20of%20waste%20by%2071%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20further%2C%20they%20also%20claim%20that%20this%20technique%20was%20also%20used%20to%20produce%20nutrient-rich%20soil%20conditioner%20(vermicompost)%20from%20invasive%20aquatic%20weeds%20like%20the%20water%20hyacinth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Mati%20Dhan%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20a%20high-quality%20organic%20vermicompost%20produced%20by%20the%20IIT%20Guwahati%20researchers%20by%20the%20novel%20two-stage%20biodegradation%20technique%20%E2%80%94%20is%20now%20available%20in%20the%20market%20and%20benefiting%20local%20farmers%2C%20according%20to%20Prof%20Kalamdhad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20institute%20transferred%20this%20technology%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farcus-www.amazon.in%2FOrganic-Vermicompost-Fertilizer-Manure-Plants%2Fdp%2FB091Q83KGD%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThis%2520compost%2520will%2520be%2520rich%2Cand%2520small%252Dscale%2520organic%2520farming.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAMER%20Private%20Ltd%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20startup%20incubated%20at%20IIT-Guwahati%2C%20which%20is%20now%20manufacturing%20%3Cem%3EMati%20Dhan%20Organic%20Vermicompost%20Fertilizer%20Manure%20for%20Plants%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20available%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farcus-www.amazon.in%2FOrganic-Vermicompost-Fertilizer-Manure-Plants%2Fdp%2FB091Q83KGD%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThis%2520compost%2520will%2520be%2520rich%2Cand%2520small%252Dscale%2520organic%2520farming.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20other%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiamart.com%2Fapshishtmanagement-environmentalresearch%2Fagriculture-vermicompost.html%2323268501673%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonline%20marketplaces%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EStudying%20waste%20management%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Professor%20Kalamdhad%20talks%20about%20dedicating%20his%20career%20to%20solid%20waste%20management.%20During%20his%20tenure%20as%20a%20professor%2C%20he%20has%20worked%20with%20many%20PhD%20students%20addressing%20a%20diverse%20range%20of%20issues%20related%20to%20solid%20waste%20management%20in%20the%20Indian%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20major%20sets%20of%20projects%20which%20stand%20out%20according%20to%20him%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1)%20Studying%20different%20techniques%20of%20composting%20of%20water%20hyacinth%20(a%20freshwater%20weed)%20given%20its%20ubiquitous%20presence%20in%20aquatic%20ecosystems%20all%20over%20Northeast%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2)%20Pilot-scale%20studies%20on%20rotary%20drum%20composting%20and%20anaerobic%20bi-phased%20baffled%20reactor%20(aka%20ABBR%2C%20which%20digests%20any%20kind%20of%20biomass)%20technology%20for%20the%20biomethanation%20(a%20process%20by%20which%20organic%20material%20is%20converted%20under%20anaerobic%20conditions%20to%20biogas)%20of%20industrial%20sludge%20and%20aquatic%20weeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20these%20projects%20received%20funding%20from%20the%20Science%20and%20Engineering%20Research%20Board%20(SERB)%20under%20the%20Department%20of%20Science%20and%20Technology%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Science%20and%20Technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20initially%20found%20that%20in%20the%20rotary%20drum%20composting%20process%2C%20accountable%20degradation%20was%20observed%20in%20the%20first%20seven%20days%20followed%20by%20the%20cooling%20phase%20of%20compost%20materials.%20These%20studies%20were%20all%20conducted%20in%20a%20batch%20scale%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Professor%20Kalamdhad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFurther%20we%20had%20also%20worked%20on%20vermicomposting%20using%20various%20worm%20cultures%20where%20we%20observed%20that%20%3Cem%3EEisenia%20fetida%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20species%20of%20earthworm)%20was%20robust%20in%20degrading%20diverse%20organic%20wastes%20including%20weed%20biomass.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20the%20results%20demonstrated%20that%20the%20vermicomposting%20process%20was%20effective%20not%20from%20day%201%20but%20from%20day%2010%20to%2015%20depending%20on%20the%20type%20of%20feed.%20The%20idea%20of%20replacing%20the%20initial%20period%20of%20the%20vermicomposting%20with%20rotary%20drum%20composting%20was%20thought%20of%20and%20studies%20were%20conducted%20accordingly%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20effort%20resulted%20in%20the%20development%20of%20the%20two-stage%20biodegradation%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Earthworms-1707743947.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Earthworms%20used%20by%20researchers%20at%20IIT%20for%20vermicompost%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Earthworms-1707743947.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Earthworms-1707743947-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Earthworms-1707743947-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Earthworms-1707743947-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Earthworms-1707743947-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341531%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EEarthworms%20used%20for%20vermicomposting%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20does%20this%20work%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOrganic%20material%20often%20makes%20up%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20municipal%20solid%20waste%20deposited%20in%20open%20dumpsites%20across%20different%20Indian%20cities%2C%20generating%20a%20lot%20of%20heat%20due%20to%20long-term%20decomposition.%20This%20poses%20serious%20environmental%20challenges%20in%20the%20long%20term.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%20to%20other%20waste%20biodegradation%20techniques%2C%20which%20require%20two%20to%20three%20months%2C%20rotary%20drum%20composting%20(RDC)%20can%20convert%20%E2%80%9Cdiverse%20organic%20feedstocks%20into%20nutrient-dense%20compost%20within%20just%2020%20days%20and%20significantly%20reduce%20the%20municipal%20waste%20volume%20by%2060%20to%2070%25%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20a%20recent%20press%20release%20issued%20by%20the%20institute.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20said%20that%2C%20RDC%20is%20known%20to%20generate%20compost%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmoderate%20quality%20as%20compared%20to%20vermicompost%20%E2%80%9D.%20Vermicomposting%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20a%20superior%20biodegradation%20process%2C%20which%20requires%20anywhere%20between%2045%20to%2060%20days.%20Given%20the%20time%20frame%20required%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F171989%2Fmadhya-pradesh-ias-indore-municipal-commissioner%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emunicipal%20corporations%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecan%E2%80%99t%20employ%20it%20on%20a%20large%20scale.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20WMRG%20under%20Professor%20Kalamdhad%20developed%20a%20unique%20two-stage%20biodegradation%20technique%20which%20combines%20the%20best%20of%20RDC%20and%20vermicomposting%20to%20reduce%20the%20duration%20of%20biodegradation.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20earthworms%2C%20%3Cem%3EEisenia%20fetida%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20can%20acclimatise%20faster%20to%20partially%20degraded%20organic%20matter%20from%20the%20drum%20compost%20and%20produce%20vermicompost%20in%20just%2027%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20product%20was%20proven%20to%20be%20non-toxic%20and%20safe%20to%20be%20used%20as%20a%20nutrient-rich%20soil%20conditioner%20(vermicompost)%20from%20waste%20with%204.2%25%20total%20nitrogen.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Preparing-the-Substrate--1707744030.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Preparing%20substrate%20for%20vermicomposting%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Preparing-the-Substrate--1707744030.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Preparing-the-Substrate--1707744030-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Preparing-the-Substrate--1707744030-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Preparing-the-Substrate--1707744030-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FIIT-Guwahati-Vermicompost-Preparing-the-Substrate--1707744030-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341532%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EResearchers%20engaged%20in%20substrate%20preparation%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20The%20Better%20India%2C%20Professor%20Kalamdhad%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20developed%20technique%20combines%20the%20thermophilic%20biodegradation%20of%20RDC%20and%20mesophilic%20biodegradation%20of%20vermicompost.%20The%20RDC%20time%20was%20studied%20to%20be%20seven%20days%2C%20and%20the%20requirement%20of%20vermicomposting%20was%2020%20days.%20We%20studied%20the%20response%20of%20the%20diverse%20organic%20waste%20with%20the%20technique%20before%20arriving%20at%20a%20conclusion.%20To%20explain%20in%20layman%E2%80%99s%20terms%2C%20if%20you%20use%20RDC%20before%20vermicomposting%2C%20it%20helps%20vermiculture%20(earthworms)%20stabilise%20the%20organic%20waste%20faster.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20employed%20all%20the%20possible%20biomasses%20for%20the%20study%2C%20majorly%20including%20vegetable%20waste%2C%20aquatic%20weeds%2C%20terrestrial%20weeds%20and%20sewage%20sludge.%20The%20experimental%20verification%20of%20this%20combined%20technique%20was%20conducted%20both%20in%20the%20laboratory%20and%20on%20a%20large%20scale%20at%20the%20Solid%20Waste%20Laboratory%20of%20IIT%20Guwahati.%20A%205%2C000-litre%20RDC%20unit%20and%20a%203%2C000-litre%20stack%20vermicomposting%20unit%20were%20established%20to%20study%20the%20large-scale%20effect%20of%20the%20process%2C%20with%20the%20moisture%20content%20controlled%20using%20horticulture%20waste%20collected%20on%20campus%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHelping%20him%20verify%20this%20technique%20is%20PhD%20student%20Mr.%20Suryateja%20Pottipati%2C%20who%20experimentally%20proved%20the%20hypothesis.%20They%20published%20the%20results%20in%20reputed%20international%20academic%20journals%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20Journal%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0956053X22001611%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBiomass%20Conversion%20and%20Biorefinery%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0301479722017625%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJournal%20of%20Environmental%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sci